<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's the glamorous Sunrise star who recently returned to full-time hosting duties.</p>

<p>And on Wednesday, Samantha Armytage enjoyed a relaxing stroll in Sydney's Rushcutters Bay with her dog Banjo.</p>

<p>The blonde beauty, 44, shared videos of herself walking her Labrador through the park and along the marina.</p>

<p>Dog's day out! Sunrise star Sam Armytage stepped out for a relaxing stroll as her pooch Banjo enjoyed a swim. Pictured is Sam with her dog Banjo on the set of Sunrise</p>

<p>'Lovely day for a walk,' she wrote in the caption of her video.</p>

<p>Sam then followed up with another clip, showing Banjo paddling through the water, before climbing up the stairs and shaking himself dry.</p>

<p>As he shook off the excess water and left Samantha soaked, she added the caption: 'Or a swim,' along with a laughing emoji.</p>

<p>'Lovely day for a walk': The blonde beauty, 44, shared videos of herself walking her Labrador through Sydney's Rushcutters Bay Park on Wednesday</p>

<p>Splash! She then followed up with another clip, showing Banjo paddling through the water, before climbing up the stairs and shaking himself dry</p>

<p>Shake it off: After Banjo shook off the excess water and left Samantha soaked, she added the caption: 'Or a swim,' along with a laughing emoji</p>

<p>Her walk with Banjo comes after it was revealed that she and David 'Kochie' Koch returned to hosting Sunrise full-time after Nine's rival program Today closed the ratings gap.</p>

<p>'They are back five days a week,' Seven News director Craig McPherson confirmed on Friday.</p>

<p>The hosts had each been enjoying a four-day working week, with Sunrise newsreader Natalie Barr filling in for Samantha on Mondays and for David on Fridays.</p>

<p>Full-time: Samantha (left) and David 'Kochie' Koch (right) have returned to hosting Sunrise full-time after Nine's rival program Today closed the ratings gap</p>

<p>Meanwhile, Samantha chose to take a step back from her on-air responsibilities in favour of a four-day working week in June. </p>

<p>David confirmed his shorter working week back in 2018, explaining 'his work schedule was taking a toll as there were other things he wanted to do'.</p>

<p>Earlier this month, Nine's Today show, fronted by Karl Stefanovic and Allison Langdon, won on the East Coast in the ratings war.</p>

<p>Steady rise: Nine's Today show, fronted by Karl Stefanovic (left) and Allison Langdon (right), recently won the East Coast in the ratings war. The once-struggling breakfast program beat Sunrise by 14,000 people, across Melbourne, Sydney and Brisbane</p>

<p>The once-struggling breakfast program beat Sunrise by 14,000 people, across Melbourne, Sydney and Brisbane.</p>

<p>These figures represent a triumphant leap in the ratings for the Today show, which had previously dragged around 70,000 viewers behind Sunrise back in June.   </p>

<p>Sunrise is still, however, the nation's most-watched breakfast TV program across the five capital cities, with a viewership of 259,000 compared to Today's 229,000. </p>

<p>Still on top! Sunrise is still, however, the nation's most-watched breakfast TV program across the five capital cities, with a viewership of 259,000 compared to Today's 229,000. Pictured left to right is Natalie Barr, Samantha, Kochie and Mark Baretta </p>
